OL,3,CVictims speak of 'traumatic' car crash
OL,4,Cmemories as drink-driver jailed
OL,6,FStaynings was also injured in the
OL,7,Fcollision and received urgent medical
OL,8,Ftreatment at Southmead Hospital, where
OL,9,Fhe also had his blood alcohol level
OL,10,Ftested.
OL,12,FHe was found to have 153 milligrams of
OL,13,Falcohol in 100 millilitres of blood -
OL,14,Falmost twice the legal limit of 80mgs.
OL,16,FIn statements provided to the judge
OL,17,Fahead of Staynings' sentencing hearing
OL,18,Fat Bristol Crown Court on 23 January,
OL,19,FChris and Jennie described the impact
OL,20,Fthe collision had and continues to
OL,21,Fhave on their lives.
