OL,3,CVictims speak of 'traumatic' car crash
OL,4,Cmemories as drink-driver jailed
OL,6,FChris told the hearing how he felt
OL,7,Flucky to be alive but 'struggled to
OL,8,Faccept' how life-changing his injuries
OL,9,Fare.
OL,11,FHe said he once lived a very active
OL,12,Flife and enjoyed surfing and skiing
OL,13,Fwith his family but he may never be
OL,14,Fable to do these activities again.
OL,16,F"The effects of the collision have
OL,17,Fpermanently and irreversibly changed
OL,18,Four lives physically and mentally for
OL,19,Fever, through no fault of our own," he
OL,20,Fsaid.
